T1jdXN0b21lci5pb1x1MDAyNnV0bV90ZXJtPWY2YzYwNjE3ZGE0MmFiZDEyYSIsImludGVybmFs=
IjoiZjZjNjA2MTdkYTQyYWJkMTJhIiwibGlua19pZCI6NDI2MDQ1fQ/1bc8c34d050a6ecf6353=
5bb4cedb7f68140325f0458bc3f18cda0f1cbf910100" style=3D"color:#d40000;text-d=
ecoration:none;font-weight:bold" class=3D"sdf">Line Sheet</a></u>, when the=
 investor relations message hit my inbox. But I couldn=E2=80=99t help mysel=
f and I quickly clicked on the email and blocked out the noise around me. A=
s I scanned the results, of course, I knew that this disastrous quarter was=
 going to inspire my partners in meaningful and important ways to figure ou=
t what exactly was going on inside WBD and how it would impact the wider in=
dustry.<br/><br/>The fate of Zaz and WBD, after all, is truly one of the gr=
eat plotlines of our era: It=E2=80=99s the tale of a big <i>but not big eno=
ugh</i> company trying to compete with trillion-dollar market cap tech gian=
ts, all while rebuilding its once steady and reliable business model to sur=
vive a far more expensive and uncertain future. I=E2=80=99ve argued in thes=
e digital pages before that CNN is an avatar for the future of the news
businesses. WBD is really a harbinger for all legacy media.<br/><br/>My par=
tners attacked this story with characteristic authority and wisdom. In <i><=
u><a href=3D"https://email.puck.news/e/c/eyJlbWFpbF9pZCI6ImRnVDJ4Z1lEQUt2Uk=
