t-weight:bold" class=3D"sdf">Sign up here</a></u>.)<br/><br/>Yes, yes, we b=
ecome obsessed with certain topics here at Puck. But the scrutiny of the Za=
z conundrum is really rooted in a larger fascination with the future of the=
 increasingly thorny media business, which now seems like it may one day be=
come a shingle of the tech industry. I=E2=80=99m
not sure that=E2=80=99s an outcome that <i>anyone</i> is prepared to fully =
contemplate, but I also don=E2=80=99t know if it=E2=80=99s enough to persua=
de the largest traditional companies to ally with one another in material w=
ays, beyond ephemeral joint ventures=E2=80=94at least not yet. My hypothesi=
s, however, is that Zaz may be the most motivated executive to figure out w=
hat a sustainable future really looks like=E2=80=94he=E2=80=99s certainly c=
ompensated with that incentive in mind=E2=80=94and, clearly, time is of the=
 essence. That race, of course, is one of the most extraordinary stories of=
 our times, and precisely what you should expect to read about in Puck.<br/=
><br/>Have a great weekend,<br/>Jon <br/></td>
